f:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX calculates JTO/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC based on the premium/discount to spot price. Rates are applied immediately to open positions with no advance notice period. The exchange uses a typical 0.01% base rate with adjustments for market conditions. Funding payments flow between long and short holders depending on whether perpetual trades above or below spot price."}]
10:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","JTO","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"JTO represents Jito's liquid staking protocol token with moderate trading volume creating funding rate inefficiencies. The token's DeFi utility and Solana ecosystem correlation generates predictable volatility patterns during network upgrades or staking reward changes. Lower liquidity compared to major pairs can lead to more pronounced funding rate deviations suitable for arbitrage strategies."}]]}]
11:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"JTO/USDT funding rates on BingX have shown correlation with Solana network activity and liquid staking demand cycles. During periods of increased staking yields or Solana validator performance improvements, positive funding rates often persist for 24-48 hours. The token exhibits heightened volatility around monthly Jito governance proposals and quarterly staking reward distributions. Weekend periods typically see reduced funding rate volatility due to lower DeFi activity, creating more stable arbitrage windows."}]]}]
12:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BingX's grid trading bots can automate JTO funding rate capture during predictable patterns around Solana ecosystem events. Copy trading features allow following successful JTO arbitrage strategies from traders with proven track records in DeFi tokens. Cross-exchange arbitrage opportunities exist between BingX and higher-liquidity venues during funding rate divergences. The 8-hour cycle provides sufficient time for position adjustment and risk management compared to more frequent funding settlements."}]]}]
13:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"JTO's moderate liquidity on BingX can lead to slippage during large position entries or exits, impacting arbitrage profitability. Sudden Solana network issues or liquid staking protocol changes can cause rapid price movements that overwhelm funding rate gains. BingX's 0.02%/0.05% maker/taker fees require funding rates above 0.1% for profitable arbitrage after transaction costs. The exchange's smaller market share means funding rates may not always reflect broader market sentiment accurately."}]]}]
14:["$","$L16",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical JTO/USDT funding rates on BingX?","answer":"JTO/USDT funding rates on BingX typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% per 8-hour period. During high Solana network activity or staking events, rates can spike to ±0.3% before normalizing within 24 hours."},{"question":"How does BingX's copy trading work for JTO funding arbitrage?","answer":"BingX allows copying successful JTO arbitrage traders automatically, replicating their position sizing and timing strategies. Copy trading fees are separate from funding rates and typically range from 5-20% of profits shared with the strategy provider."},{"question":"Can I use grid bots for automated JTO funding rate capture?","answer":"Yes, BingX's grid trading bots can automate JTO position management around funding cycles. Set tight grids around current price with position sizing that captures funding payments while minimizing directional risk exposure."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for JTO perpetuals on BingX?","answer":"BingX typically requires minimum positions of 10 JTO tokens for perpetual contracts. Check current contract specifications as minimums may adjust based on token price and market conditions."}]}]
